included.description:
â¢	Millennials are the biggest and the most diverse group globally. Indian millennials make up to 0.8 billion out of the 1.2 billion population.  By 2030 more than 60% of the Indian population will be millennials. Thus, Indian millennials will age differently as compared to other global counterparts in terms of social and cultural influences. The thesis aims to design Scenarios to help Indian Millennials predict at best their future after retirement. 
â¢	SCOPIC a mobile application to help users set preference and likings as per their choices for life after retirement. The application will predict the most likely future for the user in terms of Housing, health, environment and savings. The application will also connect the user with the relevant investment and saving plans to help plan a financially and emotionally secure future. 
â¢	The project involved systems design, generating a business model, user flows, wireframes and logic flow to attain a futuristic experience.  The application involves the use of a culturally relevant user interface and user interaction to provide the best suited scenario design.
included.title: Thesis Project: How will Indian Millennials Age
